[2] Geographical extent
Date: Mon 23 Feb 2009
Source: UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs
(OCHA), ReliefWeb, WHO report [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/rwb.nsf/db900SID/EGUA-7PKQ35?OpenDocument>


Africa weekly emergency situation update vol. 2, no. 8
------------------------------------------------------
Nigeria: outbreak of Lassa fever confirmed in Ondo and Edo States, 7
cases with 2 deaths reported (CFR: 28.5 percent).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur A-Lan Banks

[ProMED-mail thanks A-Lan Banks for responding to the moderator's
request for information identifying those Nigerian states in addition
to the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) where Lassa fever has been
reported. The states of Ondo and Edo lie to the southwest of the FCT
and Nasarawa, but are not contiguous with them.

These states can be located on the administrative map of Nigeria at
<http://www.cladiya.com/07MNIAsite/images/nigeria-map-prov.gif> - Mod.CP]
